<HEAD>Names in the News</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Subs 2nd item to CORRECT that woman is offering the piano for
sale, not selling it, for $500,000.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WISHEK, N.D. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman who won a piano once owned by the
Beatles' John Lennon is offering to sell the ebony Steinway for
$500,000.
   Sandy Dejoras said she decided to sell the piano, which she won
in a 1985 record promotion contest, after her husband died last
summer.
   She said she's received a number of offers since she advertised
in the current issue of Rolling Stone magazine.
   ``I understand the prospective bidders have included many famous
people, but so far no one has been able to get the money together,''
Ms. Dejoras said.
   Lennon was gunned down outside his New York City apartment in
1980.
</TEXT>
