<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--ResortFire     02-18 0124</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Resort Fire,0125</SECOND>
<HEAD>British Tourists Charged in Hotel Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two British tourists have been
charged with accidentally starting a fire at a ski resort last
month, a newspaper reported Saturday.
   The Vecernje Novosti daily said mechanic Ian Charles Pond and
nurse Dawn Grace were ordered to stand trial Feb. 22 on charges of
violating public safety.
   The Jan. 24 blaze at the Kopaonik ski resort gutted the top
floors of the Ras hotel and caused an estimated $635,000 damage. The
newspaper said the two had left an iron on in their hotel suite
while they were out skiing.
   Pond and Ms. Grace chose to stay at the ski resort and continue
their vacation until the trial, Vecernje Novosti said.
</TEXT>
