<HEAD>Norway Temporarily Bans Seal Pup Hunting</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OSLO, Norway (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Norwegian government has temporarily
banned seal pup hunting, a practice that has caused an international
uproar.
   The ban, imposed Friday, will last until the end of the year.
Last week, the government said it will create a commission to review
Norway's rules and regulations for seal hunting.
   A film charging that seal hunters violated the rules in 1987 and
1988 recently was shown on Swedish and British television. It showed
hunters clubbing seal pups and skinning them alive, and provoked a
wave of criticism.
