<FIRST>r a AM-FatalFire     02-18 0242</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Fatal Fire,0250</SECOND>
<HEAD>Three Children Killed in Fatal Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SPARTANBURG, S.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A father pulled four of his children
from a burning apartment early Saturday, but was unable to save
three others, who died in the blaze, authorities said.
   Killed were Amy Hames, 10; Kara Hames, 7; and Larry Hames III, 5,
said Richard Seay, deputy Spartanburg County coroner. The bodies
were found in a front bedroom.
   Amy's twin, Angela, was one of the four who survived.
   The cause of the 2:30 a.m. fire in the duplex apartment has not
been determined, but apparently it began in the living room,
authorities said.
   Darby Riggins, a neighbor who reported the fire to authorities,
said the parents and children screamed for someone to save those
inside.
   ``The mother and father were outside the house screaming and
hollering,'' Riggins said. ``There were four children ... and they
kept repeating the other children's names.''
   Larry Hames, 31, was in serious condition and his 33-year-old
wife, Monica, was in fair condition Saturday at Spartanburg Regional
Medical Center, officials said.
   Family members said Hames suffered second- and third-degree burns
on his face, arms and chest from trying to re-enter the burning
house.
   The four Hames children who were rescued by their father were
treated at the hospital and released. The children were all asleep
in the front bedroom when their father awakened them and broke a
window for the escape, said the children's grandmother, Margaree
Hames.
