<FIRST>r a AM-GangRape     02-18 0301</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Gang Rape,0311</SECOND>
<HEAD>Jury Finds Defendant Guilty in Third Rape Trial</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOEL WILLIAMS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>EDINBURG, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A jury convicted a 26-year-old man of
sexual assault Friday in the third trial stemming from the rape of a
woman who said she was abducted and repeatedly attacked by a group
of men at an illegal cockfight.
   The jury deliberated about 3{ hours before returning the verdict
against Roberto Perez shortly before 9 p.m.
   Perez is one of 10 men and a 14-year-old boy who were indicted
last April on charges ranging from kidnapping to aggravated
kidnapping to sexual assault.
   The case was moved to Hidalgo County after the defense complained
of excessive publicity in Duvall County, where the incidents
occurred.
   District Judge Ricardo Garcia gave the jury the option of
returning Saturday to assess punishment, but the jurors chose to
remain Friday night.
   Attorneys for both sides made closing arguments Friday afternoon.
   Perez testified Friday that the woman consented to sex with him
and several others on the March night of the alleged attack.
   The woman testified last week that Perez sexually assaulted her
at a ranch north of San Diego, Texas, where men were gathered for an
illegal cockfight, and then at two other locations.
   She has told authorities she was abducted while walking home and
taken to the ranch. She said she was raped and sodomized repeatedly
there and at two other locations by as many as 20 men.
   Orlando Garza, 24, the first man to be tried in the case, was
convicted on Sept. 27 of sexual assault and was sentenced to 20
years in prison by a jury in San Diego.
   Felipe Chew, 27, was convicted in San Diego on Jan. 27 of
aggravated kidnapping and was sentenced to 30 years in prison.
